71, took bronze after overpowering India Sardjoe, B-Girl India, 2-1.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9971792799292021, \"rank\": 0.002516833939473791, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qingyi_River_(Sichuan)\", \"score\": 0.6010059089231704, \"rank\": 0.4444444444444482, \"text\": \"Qingyi\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qingyi_River_(Sichuan)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qingyi_River_(Sichuan)\"}, {\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.7660196385985991, \"rank\": 0.21155704938065187, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yuasa, 25, honed her craft at Mizonokuchi Station in Kanagawa and went on to become a three-time world championships medalist before making her Olympic breakthrough on Friday.\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mizonokuchi_Station\", \"score\": 0.9999999998697149, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mizonokuchi Station\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mizonokuchi_Station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mizonokuchi_Station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B-Girl Nicka, the popular 17-year-old world champion who has a fluid style and competes with an ever present smile on her face, said she was proud to be part of the event.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We made history tonight.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking's first time at the Olympics,\\\" Banevic told Eurosport.\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am so happy people could feel our energy and see how wonderful breaking is.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More and more people will be interested in breaking now.\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a unique art form.\\\"\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking is not on the program for Los Angeles 2028, a decision Yuasa said was \\\"regretful\\\".\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1972, \"end\": 1988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would have loved to see breaking in the LA Olympics because it originated in the US,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9769197220339768, \"rank\": 0.022654758113144574, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But without Olympics, I think B-Boys and B-Girls will continue the passion of breaking, and the breaking scene will continue to be wonderful and exciting even without the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As far as the future of breaking goes, there is no problem at all.\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": []}]}"